Reasoning: The paper discusses the Neural Turing Machine, which is a machine learning model that combines neural networks and Turing machines. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also mentions tasks related to natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV), which suggest that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-categories.
